## Magnitude Analysis

- The accessories that generate the most sales by far are gloves
- The bike that sells the most is the road bike
- The total quantity of bike sold is < 700 for the entire date range (combination of all 3 bike types)
- Gloves and helmets are the top sellers (gloves 446 pairs sold)
- Bikes are premium bikes with the cheapest avg. price (mountain bike) at $1550 and most expensive (hybrid) close to $2000
- Gloves and bike lights have the highest average prices in accessories
- Texas, Florida and Carolina are the states with the most customers
- The sales channel with the highest sales revenue is “Dealer”. The lowest is “Store”
- All sales channels are selling approximately the same quantity
- All stores have approximately the same sales revenue and quantity sold.

<br>

**NOTE:** The data is not realistic (it was generated by ChatGPT); accessories such as gloves and helmets cost more than bikes.

- Although the data is not realistic, it is still usable and compatible for data model building.

